{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Establish a panel to adjudicate on disputes regarding headstones",
        "additional_details": "An error was recently made on the headstone of a family member. As it was made by the plot holder I find myself in a position of not being able to get any resolution. I have been informed I cannot put a plaque over the name to correct the mistake as this would amount to criminal damage.",
        "background": "The Government should establish a panel to adjudicate on cases where someone other than the plot holder of a burial plot would like to change the inscription on the plot\u2019s headstone. Current legislation means that only the plot owner can have the headstone changed.",
